\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And it came to pass, when Laban heard the tidings of Jacob his sister's son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house. And he told Laban all these things.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And Laban said to him, Surely thou art my bone and my flesh. And he abode with him the space of a month.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And Laban said unto Jacob, Because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought? tell me, what shall thy wages be?
