\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And Jacob said unto Laban, Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in unto her.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid for an handmaid.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And it came to pass, that in the morning, behold, it was Leah: and he said to Laban, What is this thou hast done unto me? did not I serve with thee for Rachel? wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And Laban said, It must not be so done in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Fulfil her week, and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And Jacob did so, and fulfilled her week: and he gave him Rachel his daughter to wife also.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And Laban gave to Rachel his daughter Bilhah his handmaid to be her maid.
