\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And these are the sons of Reuel Esau's son; duke Nahath, duke Zerah, duke Shammah, duke Mizzah: these are the dukes that came of Reuel in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Bashemath Esau's wife.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And these are the sons of Aholibamah Esau's wife; duke Jeush, duke Jaalam, duke Korah: these were the dukes that came of Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau's wife.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]These are the sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these are their dukes.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]These are the sons of Seir the Horite, who inhabited the land; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah,
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan: these are the dukes of the Horites, the children of Seir in the land of Edom.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And the children of Lotan were Hori and Hemam; and Lotan's sister was Timna.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And the children of Shobal were these; Alvan, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And these are the children of Zibeon; both Ajah, and Anah: this was that Anah that found the mules in the wilderness, as he fed the asses of Zibeon his father.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And the children of Anah were these; Dishon, and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And these are the children of Dishon; Hemdan, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]The children of Ezer are these; Bilhan, and Zaavan, and Akan.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]The children of Dishan are these; Uz, and Aran.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]These are the dukes that came of the Horites; duke Lotan, duke Shobal, duke Zibeon, duke Anah,
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Duke Dishon, duke Ezer, duke Dishan: these are the dukes that came of Hori, among their dukes in the land of Seir.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom, before there reigned any king over the children of Israel.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom: and the name of his city was Dinhabah.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And Jobab died, and Husham of the land of Temani reigned in his stead.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who smote Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And Samlah died, and Saul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And Saul died, and Baalhanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And Baalhanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pau; and his wife's name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And these are the names of the dukes that came of Esau, according to their families, after their places, by their names; duke Timnah, duke Alvah, duke Jetheth,
