nd it came to pass after these things, that the butler of the king of Egypt and his baker had offended their lord the king of Egypt.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And Pharaoh was wroth against two of his officers, against the chief of the butlers, and against the chief of the bakers.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And he put them in ward in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where Joseph was bound.
