\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian: and he sat down by a well.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters: and they came and drew water, and filled the troughs to water their father's flock.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And the shepherds came and drove them away: but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And when they came to Reuel their father, he said, How is it that ye are come so soon to day?
