\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And the leper in whom the plague is, his clothes shall be rent, and his head bare, and he shall put a covering upon his upper lip, and shall cry, Unclean, unclean.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]All the days wherein the plague shall be in him he shall be defiled; he is unclean: he shall dwell alone; without the camp shall his habitation be.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]The garment also that the plague of leprosy is in, whether it be a woollen garment, or a linen garment;
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Whether it be in the warp, or woof; of linen, or of woollen; whether in a skin, or in any thing made of skin;
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And if the plague be greenish or reddish in the garment, or in the skin, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any thing of skin; it is a plague of leprosy, and shall be shewed unto the priest:
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]And the priest shall look upon the plague, and shut up it that hath the plague seven days:
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]And he shall look on the plague on the seventh day: if the plague be spread in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in a skin, or in any work that is made of skin; the plague is a fretting leprosy; it is unclean.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]He shall therefore burn that garment, whether warp or woof, in woollen or in linen, or any thing of skin, wherein the plague is: for it is a fretting leprosy; it shall be burnt in the fire.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]And if the priest shall look, and, behold, the plague be not spread in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any thing of skin;
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]Then the priest shall command that they wash the thing wherein the plague is, and he shall shut it up seven days more:
\*[SUP]55\*[SUPX]And the priest shall look on the plague, after that it is washed: and, behold, if the plague have not changed his colour, and the plague be not spread; it is unclean; thou shalt burn it in the fire; it is fret inward, whether it be bare within or without.
\*[SUP]56\*[SUPX]And if the priest look, and, behold, the plague be somewhat dark after the washing of it; then he shall rend it out of the garment, or out of the skin, or out of the warp, or out of the woof:
\*[SUP]57\*[SUPX]And if it appear still in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any thing of skin; it is a spreading plague: thou shalt burn that wherein the plague is with fire.
\*[SUP]58\*[SUPX]And the garment, either warp, or woof, or whatsoever thing of skin it be, which thou shalt wash, if the plague be departed from them, then it shall be washed the second time, and shall be clean.
\*[SUP]59\*[SUPX]This is the law of the plague of leprosy in a garment of woollen or linen, either in the warp, or woof, or any thing of skins, to pronounce it clean, or to pronounce it unclean.
