\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Blind, or broken, or maimed, or having a wen, or scurvy, or scabbed, ye shall not offer these unto the Lord , nor make an offering by fire of them upon the altar unto the Lord .
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Either a bullock or a lamb that hath any thing superfluous or lacking in his parts, that mayest thou offer for a freewill offering; but for a vow it shall not be accepted.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Ye shall not offer unto the Lord that which is bruised, or crushed, or broken, or cut; neither shall ye make any offering thereof in your land.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Neither from a stranger's hand shall ye offer the bread of your God of any of these; because their corruption is in them, and blemishes be in them: they shall not be accepted for you.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]When a bullock, or a sheep, or a goat, is brought forth, then it shall be seven days under the dam; and from the eighth day and thenceforth it shall be accepted for an offering made by fire unto the Lord .
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And whether it be cow, or ewe, ye shall not kill it and her young both in one day.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And when ye will offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving unto the Lord , offer it at your own will.
