\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were forty thousand and five hundred.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And by him shall be the tribe of Manasseh: and the captain of the children of Manasseh shall be Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were thirty and two thousand and two hundred.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Then the tribe of Benjamin: and the captain of the sons of Benjamin shall be Abidan the son of Gideoni.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were thirty and five thousand and four hundred.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]All that were numbered of the camp of Ephraim were an hundred thousand and eight thousand and an hundred, throughout their armies. And they shall go forward in the third rank.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]The standard of the camp of Dan shall be on the north side by their armies: and the captain of the children of Dan shall be Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were threescore and two thousand and seven hundred.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And those that encamp by him shall be the tribe of Asher: and the captain of the children of Asher shall be Pagiel the son of Ocran.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were forty and one thousand and five hundred.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Then the tribe of Naphtali: and the captain of the children of Naphtali shall be Ahira the son of Enan.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were fifty and three thousand and four hundred.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]All they that were numbered in the camp of Dan were an hundred thousand and fifty and seven thousand and six hundred. They shall go hindmost with their standards.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]These are those which were numbered of the children of Israel by the house of their fathers: all those that were numbered of the camps throughout their hosts were six hundred thousand and three thousand and five hundred and fifty.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]But the Levites were not numbered among the children of Israel; as the Lord commanded Moses.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And the children of Israel did according to all that the Lord commanded Moses: so they pitched by their standards, and so they set forward, every one after their families, according to the house of their fathers.
