hese also are the generations of Aaron and Moses in the day that the Lord spake with Moses in mount Sinai.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And these are the names of the sons of Aaron; Nadab the firstborn, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]These are the names of the sons of Aaron, the priests which were anointed, whom he consecrated to minister in the priest's office.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And Nadab and Abihu died before the Lord , when they offered strange fire before the Lord , in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children: and Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest's office in the sight of Aaron their father.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Bring the tribe of Levi near, and present them before Aaron the priest, that they may minister unto him.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]And they shall keep his charge, and the charge of the whole congregation before the tabernacle of the congregation, to do the service of the tabernacle.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And they shall keep all the instruments of the tabernacle of the congregation, and the charge of the children of Israel, to do the service of the tabernacle.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And thou shalt give the Levites unto Aaron and to his sons: they are wholly given unto him out of the children of Israel.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And thou shalt appoint Aaron and his sons, and they shall wait on their priest's office: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And I, behold, I have taken the Levites from among the children of Israel instead of all the firstborn that openeth the matrix among the children of Israel: therefore the Levites shall be mine;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Because all the firstborn are mine; for on the day that I smote all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I hallowed unto me all the firstborn in Israel, both man and beast: mine shall they be: I am the Lord .
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And the Lord spake unto Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, saying,
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Number the children of Levi after the house of their fathers, by their families: every male from a month old and upward shalt thou number them.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And Moses numbered them according to the word of the Lord , as he was commanded.
