nd when Balaam saw that it pleased the Lord to bless Israel, he went not, as at other times, to seek for enchantments, but he set his face toward the wilderness.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel abiding in his tents according to their tribes; and the spirit of God came upon him.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]He hath said, which heard the words of God, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]How goodly are thy tents, O Jacob, and thy tabernacles, O Israel!
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]As the valleys are they spread forth, as gardens by the river's side, as the trees of lign aloes which the Lord hath planted, and as cedar trees beside the waters.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]He shall pour the water out of his buckets, and his seed shall be in many waters, and his king shall be higher than Agag, and his kingdom shall be exalted.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]God brought him forth out of Egypt; he hath as it were the strength of an unicorn: he shall eat up the nations his enemies, and shall break their bones, and pierce them through with his arrows.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]He couched, he lay down as a lion, and as a great lion: who shall stir him up? Blessed is he that blesseth thee, and cursed is he that curseth thee.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And Balak's anger was kindled against Balaam, and he smote his hands together: and Balak said unto Balaam, I called thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast altogether blessed them these three times.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Therefore now flee thou to thy place: I thought to promote thee unto great honour; but, lo, the Lord hath kept thee back from honour.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And Balaam said unto Balak, Spake I not also to thy messengers which thou sentest unto me, saying,
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the commandment of the Lord , to do either good or bad of mine own mind; but what the Lord saith, that will I speak?
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And now, behold, I go unto my people: come therefore, and I will advertise thee what this people shall do to thy people in the latter days.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]He hath said, which heard the words of God, and knew the knowledge of the most High, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]I shall see him, but not now: I shall behold him, but not nigh: there shall come a Star out of Jacob, and a Sceptre shall rise out of Israel, and shall smite the corners of Moab, and destroy all the children of Sheth.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And Edom shall be a possession, Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies; and Israel shall do valiantly.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Out of Jacob shall come he that shall have dominion, and shall destroy him that remaineth of the city.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And when he looked on Amalek, he took up his parable, and said, Amalek was the first of the nations; but his latter end shall be that he perish for ever.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And he looked on the Kenites, and took up his parable, and said, Strong is thy dwellingplace, and thou puttest thy nest in a rock.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Nevertheless the Kenite shall be wasted, until Asshur shall carry thee away captive.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And he took up his parable, and said, Alas, who shall live when God doeth this!
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And ships shall come from the coast of Chittim, and shall afflict Asshur, and shall afflict Eber, and he also shall perish for ever.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And Balaam rose up, and went and returned to his place: and Balak also went his way.
