nd Moses called all Israel, and said unto them, Hear, O Israel, the statutes and judgments which I speak in your ears this day, that ye may learn them, and keep, and do them.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]The Lord our God made a covenant with us in Horeb.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]The Lord made not this covenant with our fathers, but with us, even us, who are all of us here alive this day.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]The Lord talked with you face to face in the mount out of the midst of the fire,
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX](I stood between the Lord and you at that time, to shew you the word of the Lord : for ye were afraid by reason of the fire, and went not up into the mount;) saying,
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]I am the Lord thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage.
