\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And David spake unto the Lord when he saw the angel that smote the people, and said, Lo, I have sinned, and I have done wickedly: but these sheep, what have they done? let thine hand, I pray thee, be against me, and against my father's house.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And Gad came that day to David, and said unto him, Go up, rear an altar unto the Lord in the threshingfloor of Araunah the Jebusite.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And David, according to the saying of Gad, went up as the Lord commanded.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And Araunah looked, and saw the king and his servants coming on toward him: and Araunah went out, and bowed himself before the king on his face upon the ground.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And Araunah said, Wherefore is my lord the king come to his servant? And David said, To buy the threshingfloor of thee, to build an altar unto the Lord , that the plague may be stayed from the people.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And Araunah said unto David, Let my lord the king take and offer up what seemeth good unto him: behold, here be oxen for burnt sacrifice, and threshing instruments and other instruments of the oxen for wood.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]All these things did Araunah, as a king, give unto the king. And Araunah said unto the king, The Lord thy God accept thee.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And the king said unto Araunah, Nay; but I will surely buy it of thee at a price: neither will I offer burnt offerings unto the Lord my God of that which doth cost me nothing. So David bought the threshingfloor and the oxen for fifty shekels of silver.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And David built there an altar unto the Lord , and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. So the Lord was intreated for the land, and the plague was stayed from Israel.
