\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]After it a voice roareth: he thundereth with the voice of his excellency; and he will not stay them when his voice is heard.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]God thundereth marvellously with his voice; great things doeth he, which we cannot comprehend.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]For he saith to the snow, Be thou on the earth; likewise to the small rain, and to the great rain of his strength.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]He sealeth up the hand of every man; that all men may know his work.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Then the beasts go into dens, and remain in their places.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Out of the south cometh the whirlwind: and cold out of the north.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]By the breath of God frost is given: and the breadth of the waters is straitened.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Also by watering he wearieth the thick cloud: he scattereth his bright cloud:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And it is turned round about by his counsels: that they may do whatsoever he commandeth them upon the face of the world in the earth.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]He causeth it to come, whether for correction, or for his land, or for mercy.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Hearken unto this, O Job: stand still, and consider the wondrous works of God.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Dost thou know when God disposed them, and caused the light of his cloud to shine?
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Dost thou know the balancings of the clouds, the wondrous works of him which is perfect in knowledge?
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]How thy garments are warm, when he quieteth the earth by the south wind?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Hast thou with him spread out the sky, which is strong, and as a molten looking glass?
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Teach us what we shall say unto him; for we cannot order our speech by reason of darkness.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Shall it be told him that I speak? if a man speak, surely he shall be swallowed up.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And now men see not the bright light which is in the clouds: but the wind passeth, and cleanseth them.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Fair weather cometh out of the north: with God is terrible majesty.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Touching the Almighty, we cannot find him out: he is excellent in power, and in judgment, and in plenty of justice: he will not afflict.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Men do therefore fear him: he respecteth not any that are wise of heart.
