\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Knowest thou it, because thou wast then born? or because the number of thy days is great?
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail,
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]By what way is the light parted, which scattereth the east wind upon the earth?
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Who hath divided a watercourse for the overflowing of waters, or a way for the lightning of thunder;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]To cause it to rain on the earth, where no man is; on the wilderness, wherein there is no man;
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]To satisfy the desolate and waste ground; and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth?
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Hath the rain a father? or who hath begotten the drops of dew?
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Out of whose womb came the ice? and the hoary frost of heaven, who hath gendered it?
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]The waters are hid as with a stone, and the face of the deep is frozen.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Canst thou bind the sweet influences of Pleiades, or loose the bands of Orion?
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Canst thou bring forth Mazzaroth in his season? or canst thou guide Arcturus with his sons?
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth?
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds, that abundance of waters may cover thee?
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]Canst thou send lightnings, that they may go and say unto thee, Here we are?
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts? or who hath given understanding to the heart?
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]Who can number the clouds in wisdom? or who can stay the bottles of heaven,
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]When the dust groweth into hardness, and the clods cleave fast together?
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Wilt thou hunt the prey for the lion? or fill the appetite of the young lions,
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]When they couch in their dens, and abide in the covert to lie in wait?
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Who provideth for the raven his food? when his young ones cry unto God, they wander for lack of meat.
