\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Wilt thou trust him, because his strength is great? or wilt thou leave thy labour to him?
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather it into thy barn?
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Gavest thou the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich?
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust,
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not her's: her labour is in vain without fear;
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Because God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he imparted to her understanding.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]What time she lifteth up herself on high, she scorneth the horse and his rider.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Hast thou given the horse strength? hast thou clothed his neck with thunder?
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Canst thou make him afraid as a grasshopper? the glory of his nostrils is terrible.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in his strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]The quiver rattleth against him, the glittering spear and the shield.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]He swalloweth the ground with fierceness and rage: neither believeth he that it is the sound of the trumpet.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]He saith among the trumpets, Ha, ha; and he smelleth the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Doth the hawk fly by thy wisdom, and stretch her wings toward the south?
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Doth the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest on high?
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]From thence she seeketh the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain are, there is she.
