\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For he hath broken the gates of brass, and cut the bars of iron in sunder.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat; and they draw near unto the gates of death.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saveth them out of their distresses.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them from their destructions.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]These see the works of the Lord , and his wonders in the deep.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]For he commandeth, and raiseth the stormy wind, which lifteth up the waves thereof.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wit's end.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]He maketh the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]He turneth the wilderness into a standing water, and dry ground into watersprings.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]He poureth contempt upon princes, and causeth them to wander in the wilderness, where there is no way.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh him families like a flock.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]The righteous shall see it, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]Whoso is wise, and will observe these things, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the Lord .
