\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]My hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]Remember the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]This is my comfort in my affliction: for thy word hath quickened me.
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]The proud have had me greatly in derision: yet have I not declined from thy law.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]I remembered thy judgments of old, O Lord ; and have comforted myself.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]Horror hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]Thy statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.
\*[SUP]55\*[SUPX]I have remembered thy name, O Lord , in the night, and have kept thy law.
\*[SUP]56\*[SUPX]This I had, because I kept thy precepts.
\*[SUP]57\*[SUPX]Thou art my portion, O Lord : I have said that I would keep thy words.
\*[SUP]58\*[SUPX]I intreated thy favour with my whole heart: be merciful unto me according to thy word.
\*[SUP]59\*[SUPX]I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]60\*[SUPX]I made haste, and delayed not to keep thy commandments.
\*[SUP]61\*[SUPX]The bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten thy law.
\*[SUP]62\*[SUPX]At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.
\*[SUP]63\*[SUPX]I am a companion of all them that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.
\*[SUP]64\*[SUPX]The earth, O Lord , is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.
\*[SUP]65\*[SUPX]Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O Lord , according unto thy word.
\*[SUP]66\*[SUPX]Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.
\*[SUP]67\*[SUPX]Before I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept thy word.
\*[SUP]68\*[SUPX]Thou art good, and doest good; teach me thy statutes.
\*[SUP]69\*[SUPX]The proud have forged a lie against me: but I will keep thy precepts with my whole heart.
\*[SUP]70\*[SUPX]Their heart is as fat as grease; but I delight in thy law.
\*[SUP]71\*[SUPX]It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.
\*[SUP]72\*[SUPX]The law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.
\*[SUP]73\*[SUPX]Thy hands have made me and fashioned me: give me understanding, that I may learn thy commandments.
\*[SUP]74\*[SUPX]They that fear thee will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in thy word.
\*[SUP]75\*[SUPX]I know, O Lord , that thy judgments are right, and that thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me.
\*[SUP]76\*[SUPX]Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant.
\*[SUP]77\*[SUPX]Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law is my delight.
\*[SUP]78\*[SUPX]Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in thy precepts.
\*[SUP]79\*[SUPX]Let those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]80\*[SUPX]Let my heart be sound in thy statutes; that I be not ashamed.
\*[SUP]81\*[SUPX]My soul fainteth for thy salvation: but I hope in thy word.
\*[SUP]82\*[SUPX]Mine eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me?
\*[SUP]83\*[SUPX]For I am become like a bottle in the smoke; yet do I not forget thy statutes.
\*[SUP]84\*[SUPX]How many are the days of thy servant? when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me?
\*[SUP]85\*[SUPX]The proud have digged pits for me, which are not after thy law.
\*[SUP]86\*[SUPX]All thy commandments are faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help thou me.
\*[SUP]87\*[SUPX]They had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not thy precepts.
\*[SUP]88\*[SUPX]Quicken me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.
\*[SUP]89\*[SUPX]For ever, O Lord , thy word is settled in heaven.
\*[SUP]90\*[SUPX]Thy faithfulness is unto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.
\*[SUP]91\*[SUPX]They continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all are thy servants.
\*[SUP]92\*[SUPX]Unless thy law had been my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.
\*[SUP]93\*[SUPX]I will never forget thy precepts: for with them thou hast quickened me.
\*[SUP]94\*[SUPX]I am thine, save me: for I have sought thy precepts.
\*[SUP]95\*[SUPX]The wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]96\*[SUPX]I have seen an end of all perfection: but thy commandment is exceeding broad.
\*[SUP]97\*[SUPX]O how love I thy law! it is my meditation all the day.
\*[SUP]98\*[SUPX]Thou through thy commandments hast made me wiser than mine enemies: for they are ever with me.
\*[SUP]99\*[SUPX]I have more understanding than all my teachers: for thy testimonies are my meditation.
\*[SUP]100\*[SUPX]I understand more than the ancients, because I keep thy precepts.
\*[SUP]101\*[SUPX]I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.
\*[SUP]102\*[SUPX]I have not departed from thy judgments: for thou hast taught me.
\*[SUP]103\*[SUPX]How sweet are thy words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
\*[SUP]104\*[SUPX]Through thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.
\*[SUP]105\*[SUPX]Thy word is a lamp unto my feet, and a light unto my path.
\*[SUP]106\*[SUPX]I have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.
\*[SUP]107\*[SUPX]I am afflicted very much: quicken me, O Lord , according unto thy word.
\*[SUP]108\*[SUPX]Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O Lord , and teach me thy judgments.
\*[SUP]109\*[SUPX]My soul is continually in my hand: yet do I not forget thy law.
\*[SUP]110\*[SUPX]The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.
\*[SUP]111\*[SUPX]Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage for ever: for they are the rejoicing of my heart.
\*[SUP]112\*[SUPX]I have inclined mine heart to perform thy statutes alway, even unto the end.
\*[SUP]113\*[SUPX]I hate vain thoughts: but thy law do I love.
\*[SUP]114\*[SUPX]Thou art my hiding place and my shield: I hope in thy word.
\*[SUP]115\*[SUPX]Depart from me, ye evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.
\*[SUP]116\*[SUPX]Uphold me according unto thy word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.
\*[SUP]117\*[SUPX]Hold thou me up, and I shall be safe: and I will have respect unto thy statutes continually.
\*[SUP]118\*[SUPX]Thou hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes: for their deceit is falsehood.
\*[SUP]119\*[SUPX]Thou puttest away all the wicked of the earth like dross: therefore I love thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]120\*[SUPX]My flesh trembleth for fear of thee; and I am afraid of thy judgments.
\*[SUP]121\*[SUPX]I have done judgment and justice: leave me not to mine oppressors.
\*[SUP]122\*[SUPX]Be surety for thy servant for good: let not the proud oppress me.
\*[SUP]123\*[SUPX]Mine eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.
\*[SUP]124\*[SUPX]Deal with thy servant according unto thy mercy, and teach me thy statutes.
\*[SUP]125\*[SUPX]I am thy servant; give me understanding, that I may know thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]126\*[SUPX]It is time for thee, Lord , to work: for they have made void thy law.
\*[SUP]127\*[SUPX]Therefore I love thy commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.
\*[SUP]128\*[SUPX]Therefore I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right; and I hate every false way.
\*[SUP]129\*[SUPX]Thy testimonies are wonderful: therefore doth my soul keep them.
\*[SUP]130\*[SUPX]The entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple.
\*[SUP]131\*[SUPX]I opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for thy commandments.
\*[SUP]132\*[SUPX]Look thou upon me, and be merciful unto me, as thou usest to do unto those that love thy name.
\*[SUP]133\*[SUPX]Order my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.
\*[SUP]134\*[SUPX]Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.
\*[SUP]135\*[SUPX]Make thy face to shine upon thy servant; and teach me thy statutes.
\*[SUP]136\*[SUPX]Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.
\*[SUP]137\*[SUPX]Righteous art thou, O Lord , and upright are thy judgments.
\*[SUP]138\*[SUPX]Thy testimonies that thou hast commanded are righteous and very faithful.
\*[SUP]139\*[SUPX]My zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words.
\*[SUP]140\*[SUPX]Thy word is very pure: therefore thy servant loveth it.
\*[SUP]141\*[SUPX]I am small and despised: yet do not I forget thy precepts.
\*[SUP]142\*[SUPX]Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and thy law is the truth.
\*[SUP]143\*[SUPX]Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me: yet thy commandments are my delights.
\*[SUP]144\*[SUPX]The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.
\*[SUP]145\*[SUPX]I cried with my whole heart; hear me, O Lord : I will keep thy statutes.
\*[SUP]146\*[SUPX]I cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]147\*[SUPX]I prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in thy word.
\*[SUP]148\*[SUPX]Mine eyes prevent the night watches, that I might meditate in thy word.
\*[SUP]149\*[SUPX]Hear my voice according unto thy lovingkindness: O Lord , quicken me according to thy judgment.
\*[SUP]150\*[SUPX]They draw nigh that follow after mischief: they are far from thy law.
\*[SUP]151\*[SUPX]Thou art near, O Lord ; and all thy commandments are truth.
\*[SUP]152\*[SUPX]Concerning thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them for ever.
\*[SUP]153\*[SUPX]Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.
\*[SUP]154\*[SUPX]Plead my cause, and deliver me: quicken me according to thy word.
\*[SUP]155\*[SUPX]Salvation is far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.
\*[SUP]156\*[SUPX]Great are thy tender mercies, O Lord : quicken me according to thy judgments.
\*[SUP]157\*[SUPX]Many are my persecutors and mine enemies; yet do I not decline from thy testimonies.
\*[SUP]158\*[SUPX]I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not thy word.
\*[SUP]159\*[SUPX]Consider how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O Lord , according to thy lovingkindness.
\*[SUP]160\*[SUPX]Thy word is true from the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth for ever.
\*[SUP]161\*[SUPX]Princes have persecuted me without a cause: but my heart standeth in awe of thy word.
\*[SUP]162\*[SUPX]I rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.
\*[SUP]163\*[SUPX]I hate and abhor lying: but thy law do I love.
\*[SUP]164\*[SUPX]Seven times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.
\*[SUP]165\*[SUPX]Great peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them.
\*[SUP]166\*[SUPX]Lord , I have hoped for thy salvation, and done thy commandments.
\*[SUP]167\*[SUPX]My soul hath kept thy testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.
\*[SUP]168\*[SUPX]I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways are before thee.
\*[SUP]169\*[SUPX]Let my cry come near before thee, O Lord : give me understanding according to thy word.
\*[SUP]170\*[SUPX]Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.
\*[SUP]171\*[SUPX]My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.
\*[SUP]172\*[SUPX]My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments are righteousness.
\*[SUP]173\*[SUPX]Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.
\*[SUP]174\*[SUPX]I have longed for thy salvation, O Lord ; and thy law is my delight.
\*[SUP]175\*[SUPX]Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.
\*[SUP]176\*[SUPX]I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 120"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "I" 2 COND 90
