\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For thy servant David's sake turn not away the face of thine anointed.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]The Lord hath sworn in truth unto David; he will not turn from it; Of the fruit of thy body will I set upon thy throne.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]If thy children will keep my covenant and my testimony that I shall teach them, their children shall also sit upon thy throne for evermore.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]For the Lord hath chosen Zion; he hath desired it for his habitation.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]This is my rest for ever: here will I dwell; for I have desired it.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]I will abundantly bless her provision: I will satisfy her poor with bread.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]I will also clothe her priests with salvation: and her saints shall shout aloud for joy.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]There will I make the horn of David to bud: I have ordained a lamp for mine anointed.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]His enemies will I clothe with shame: but upon himself shall his crown flourish.
