\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For they shall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And they lay wait for their own blood; they lurk privily for their own lives.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets:
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, saying,
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the Lord :
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.
