\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Honour the Lord with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord ; neither be weary of his correction:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]For whom the Lord loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that getteth understanding.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]She is more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is every one that retaineth her.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]The Lord by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]For the Lord shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]For the froward is abomination to the Lord : but his secret is with the righteous.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.
