\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Forsake her not, and she shall preserve thee: love her, and she shall keep thee.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Exalt her, and she shall promote thee: she shall bring thee to honour, when thou dost embrace her.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]She shall give to thine head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings; and the years of thy life shall be many.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]I have taught thee in the way of wisdom; I have led thee in right paths.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Take fast hold of instruction; let her not go: keep her; for she is thy life.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil men.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For they sleep not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause some to fall.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]But the path of the just is as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]The way of the wicked is as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]My son, attend to my words; incline thine ear unto my sayings.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thine heart.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]For they are life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Keep thy heart with all diligence; for out of it are the issues of life.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Put away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy foot from evil.
