\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours be in the house of a stranger;
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!
