y son, if thou be surety for thy friend, if thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.
