oth not wisdom cry? and understanding put forth her voice?
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]She standeth in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]She crieth at the gates, at the entry of the city, at the coming in at the doors.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice is to the sons of man.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]O ye simple, understand wisdom: and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and the opening of my lips shall be right things.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]All the words of my mouth are in righteousness; there is nothing froward or perverse in them.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]They are all plain to him that understandeth, and right to them that find knowledge.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Receive my instruction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For wisdom is better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge of witty inventions.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]The fear of the Lord is to hate evil: pride, and arrogancy, and the evil way, and the froward mouth, do I hate.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Counsel is mine, and sound wisdom: I am understanding; I have strength.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Riches and honour are with me; yea, durable riches and righteousness.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my revenue than choice silver.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]I lead in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of judgment:
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance; and I will fill their treasures.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]The Lord possessed me in the beginning of his way, before his works of old.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, or ever the earth was.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Before the mountains were settled, before the hills was I brought forth:
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]While as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the highest part of the dust of the world.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]When he prepared the heavens, I was there: when he set a compass upon the face of the depth:
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]When he established the clouds above: when he strengthened the fountains of the deep:
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]When he gave to the sea his decree, that the waters should not pass his commandment: when he appointed the foundations of the earth:
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Then I was by him, as one brought up with him: and I was daily his delight, rejoicing always before him;
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights were with the sons of men.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children: for blessed are they that keep my ways.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Blessed is the man that heareth me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]For whoso findeth me findeth life, and shall obtain favour of the Lord .
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul: all they that hate me love death.
