\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]So Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them, and brought them to the king of Babylon to Riblah.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And the king of Babylon smote them, and put them to death in Riblah in the land of Hamath. Thus Judah was carried away captive out of his own land.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]This is the people whom Nebuchadrezzar carried away captive: in the seventh year three thousand Jews and three and twenty:
